Detailed Description

This is a standard kalman filter implementation.

This class holds necessary methods to keep track of objects that are defined as tracks. Mostly eigen library is referred to carry out matrix operations. System model is assumed to be linear and time-invariant. This filter works by continously forming a prediction at each new timestep, and updating that prediction whenever a new information arrives from a sensor. How sensor information is relayed to this filter is not a concern of this class.
